# Real-Time Cloudburst Prediction System for Babusar Top, Kaghan Valley
## Technical Explanation for Thesis / Supervisor Review

> **Location:** Babusar Top, Kaghan Valley — Coordinates 35.6°N, 73.6°E  
> **Model:** Bidirectional Long Short-Term Memory (BiLSTM) Neural Network  
> **Data Period:** 2014–2023 (ERA5 Reanalysis + Total Precipitation)  
> **Deployment:** Real-time Flask web dashboard with live Open-Meteo API integration

---

## 1. Problem Statement

Cloudbursts — defined as extreme rainfall events exceeding **20 mm/hour** — are among the most dangerous hydrometeorological hazards in mountainous regions. Babusar Top in the Kaghan Valley (KPK, Pakistan) is particularly vulnerable due to its high altitude (~4,173 m), steep terrain, and exposure to monsoon and western disturbance moisture. Cloudbursts at this location cause flash floods, landslides, road blockages, and loss of life.

Traditional Numerical Weather Prediction (NWP) models have limited spatial resolution and do not perform well for localised extreme events in complex mountain terrain. This project addresses that gap by building a **data-driven deep learning model** capable of predicting cloudburst probability up to **2 hours in advance** using atmospheric reanalysis data.

