## 2. Dataset

### 2.1 ERA5 Atmospheric Reanalysis Data
The primary dataset is ERA5 reanalysis data obtained from the **European Centre for Medium-Range Weather Forecasts (ECMWF)** via the Copernicus Climate Data Store (CDS). ERA5 is the gold standard global atmospheric reanalysis dataset with:
- **Spatial resolution:** 0.25° × 0.25° (~28 km)
- **Temporal resolution:** Hourly
- **Coverage:** 2014–2023 for the Babusar Top region

**Pressure-level variables** were extracted at three atmospheric levels: **500 hPa** (upper troposphere), **700 hPa** (mid troposphere), and **850 hPa** (lower troposphere).

| Variable | Symbol | Levels | Physical Meaning |
|---|---|---|---|
| Relative Humidity | r | 500, 700, 850 hPa | Moisture content at different heights |
| Temperature | t | 500, 700, 850 hPa | Atmospheric temperature at pressure levels |
| U-component of Wind | u | 500, 700, 850 hPa | East-West wind speed |
| V-component of Wind | v | 500, 700, 850 hPa | North-South wind speed |
| Vertical Velocity | vv | 500, 700, 850 hPa | Upward/downward air motion (key for convection) |

**Surface variables** were also included:

| Variable | Symbol | Physical Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| 2m Temperature | t2m | Near-surface air temperature |
| 2m Dewpoint Temperature | d2m | Moisture near surface |
| Surface Pressure | sp | Atmospheric pressure at surface |
| Total Cloud Cover | tcc | Fractional cloud coverage |
| Convective Available Potential Energy | cape | Energy available for storm formation |
| Total Column Water Vapour | tcwv | Total precipitable water in the column |

### 2.2 Total Precipitation (TP) Data
Hourly total precipitation (mm/hr) data was sourced separately and merged with the ERA5 dataset. The `tp` variable (in metres) was converted to **mm/hr** (`tp × 1000`).

### 2.3 Dataset Statistics (After Preprocessing)
- **ERA5 raw shape:** 701,184 rows × 15 columns
- **TP raw shape:** 5,465,855 rows × 4 columns
- **After merging and cleaning:** 61,998 hourly records × 25 features
- **Final feature count:** 26 (including 4 cyclical time features)
- **Total sequences created:** 61,984 sequences of shape [(6 timesteps, 26 features)](file:///c:/Users/HYPER%20Computers/Downloads/a4.project.bilstm/app.py#53-59)

