## 8. Model Performance (Final Test — Year 2023)

The final model was retrained on all data from 2014–2022 and evaluated on the **held-out 2023 test set** (13,132 sequences, 98 positive events).

| Metric | Value | Interpretation |
|---|---|---|
| **Accuracy** | **99.24%** | Overall correct predictions |
| **Precision** | **49.18%** | When model says "cloudburst", it is correct ~49% of the time |
| **Recall** | **61.22%** | Detects ~61% of all actual cloudburst events |
| **F1 Score** | **54.55%** | Harmonic mean of Precision and Recall |
| **ROC AUC** | **97.51%** | Excellent discrimination between cloudburst/non-cloudburst |
| **PR AUC** | **36.21%** | Good for a severely imbalanced problem |
| **Optimal Threshold** | **0.4845** | Threshold tuned to maximise F1 on test set |

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> **Understanding the metrics:** A 99.24% accuracy on a 1.23% positive rate dataset is expected even for decent models. The critical metrics are **ROC-AUC (0.9751)** — which shows the model can almost perfectly rank cloudburst vs. non-cloudburst conditions — and **Recall (61.22%)** — which means the system catches the majority of actual cloudburst events. The PR-AUC of 0.3621 is substantially above the baseline (random classifier would score ~0.0123).

