The system classifies predictions into three operational risk levels inspired by standard meteorological warning systems:

| Risk Level | Probability Range | Color | Action |
|---|---|---|---|
| ✓ **Low Risk** | 0% – 35% | 🟢 Green | Normal conditions |
| ⚠️ **Moderate Risk** | 36% – 60% | 🟡 Yellow | Stay alert, monitor conditions |
| 🚨 **High Risk** | 61% – 100% | 🔴 Red | Multi-tone alarm + "Stay alert and avoid flood prone areas!" |

