## 11. Live Web Dashboard System Architecture

The deployment system is a full-stack web application built with:

### 11.1 Backend — Python Flask ([app.py](file:///c:/Users/HYPER%20Computers/Downloads/a4.project.bilstm/app.py))
- **Framework:** Flask (Python 3.x)
- **Model Loading:** TensorFlow/Keras with custom focal_loss objects
- **Scaler:** scikit-learn `StandardScaler` loaded from [scaler_final.pkl](file:///c:/Users/HYPER%20Computers/Downloads/a4.project.bilstm/scaler_final.pkl)
- **Feature Columns:** 26 feature names loaded from [feature_cols.pkl](file:///c:/Users/HYPER%20Computers/Downloads/a4.project.bilstm/feature_cols.pkl)
- **API Security:** API key authentication via `X-API-Key` HTTP header
- **Rate Limiting:** 300 requests per 60-second window (in-memory)
- **Timezone:** Asia/Karachi (UTC+5:00, Pakistan Standard Time)

### 11.2 Key API Endpoints

| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `GET /` | GET | Serve the dashboard HTML |
| `POST /api/predict_live` | POST (authenticated) | Accept live ERA5-format weather features, run model, return probability + 6h forecast |
| `POST /api/predict` | POST | Direct feature array prediction (raw 2D/3D input) |
| `GET /api/health` | GET | Server health check |
| `GET /api/prediction` | GET | Quick prediction using placeholder features |

### 11.3 Frontend — HTML/CSS/JavaScript ([templates/index.html](file:///c:/Users/HYPER%20Computers/Downloads/a4.project.bilstm/templates/index.html))
The dashboard is a single-page application (no framework) featuring:

- **Live Prediction Loop:** A self-chaining `async/await` loop ([startLiveLoop](file:///c:/Users/HYPER%20Computers/Downloads/a4.project.bilstm/templates/index.html#1235-1246)) that runs predictions back-to-back, updating approximately **every 1 second**
- **Weather Data:** Fetched from **Open-Meteo API** (free, no API key required) every 60 seconds and cached to avoid API rate limiting
- **External Weather API:** WeatherAPI.com with API key (fallback to Open-Meteo)
- **Map:** Interactive **Leaflet.js** map centered on Babusar Top with a colour-coded risk marker
- **Alerts:** Browser notification API + audio beep (Web Audio API) for high-risk events
- **Clock:** Live Pakistan Standard Time clock updating every second

### 11.4 Live Feature Pipeline (How Real-Time Prediction Works)

```
Open-Meteo API (every 60s)
        ↓
fetchOpenMeteoFeatures()
  - Fetches hourly: temperature, dewpoint, surface pressure,
    cloud cover, CAPE, and pressure-level wind/humidity/temp
  - Converts wind speed + direction → U/V components
  - Converts temperatures °C → Kelvin (for consistency with ERA5 training data)
  - Builds 10 rows of feature dictionaries (covering ±6 hours around current time)
        ↓
Cached in browser for 60 seconds
        ↓
POST /api/predict_live  (with X-API-Key header)
  - Flask receives feature rows
  - Maps to the 26 saved feature columns (in exact training order)
  - Applies saved StandardScaler (same transform used in training)
  - Reshapes to (1, 6, 26) → BiLSTM model → sigmoid output
  - Generates 6-hour forecast array
        ↓
Dashboard updates: risk badge, probability %, forecast cards,
weather variables, map marker colour
```

