## 14. Summary

This project presents a complete end-to-end **deep learning-based early warning system** for cloud burst prediction at Babusar Top:

- **Data:** 10 years (2014–2023) of hourly ERA5 atmospheric reanalysis + precipitation data; 61,998 hourly records; 26 meteorological features
- **Model:** BiLSTM (171,105 parameters) trained with Focal Loss and balanced class weights on a 82:1 imbalanced dataset
- **Training:** 30-trial random hyperparameter search evaluated via temporal rolling-window cross-validation (to prevent data leakage)
- **Performance on 2023 test set:** Accuracy 99.24%, Recall 61.22%, ROC-AUC 97.51%, PR-AUC 36.21%
- **Lead Time:** 2-hour ahead prediction with a 6-hour forecast extension
- **Deployment:** Real-time Flask REST API server with live Open-Meteo integration, interactive Leaflet.js map, and three-tier colour-coded risk alert system
- **Update Rate:** ~1 prediction per second, truly live dashboard

This system demonstrates the feasibility of applying modern deep learning (BiLSTM) to a high-stakes, real-world early warning problem in a data-scarce, heavily imbalanced setting, achieving strong discriminative performance (ROC-AUC 0.9751) that can meaningfully support disaster risk reduction in the Kaghan Valley.
